{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GmHc9N8Srjnat2yn1mzYfx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite Codebase\n\nI've thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase and gathered complete information about the current state of the system. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Directory Layout:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/` - Main source code\n  - `cli/` - Command-line interface handlers (config, daemon, flow, init, project, requirements, run)\n  - `adapters/` - Filesystem, worktree, and stub backend adapters\n  - `contexts/` - Domain-specific contexts:\n    - `agent_execution/` - Backend invocation and session management\n    - `automation_runtime/` - Daemon task, lease, routing, and loop management\n    - `conformance_spec/` - Conformance feature specifications\n    - `project_run_record/` - Journal, snapshots, and run records\n    - `requirements_drafting/` - Requirements contracts and models\n    - `workflow_composition/` - Workflow engine, flow definitions, stage plans\n    - `workspace_governance/` - Workspace and project configuration\n  - `shared/` - Domain types (FlowPreset, StageId, error types)\n\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/` - Test suite\n  - `cli.rs` - Integration tests for CLI commands (3609 lines)\n  - `unit/` - Unit tests for core logic\n  - `conformance/features/` - Gherkin-based feature specifications (BDD tests)\n\n### 2. QUICK_DEV SUPPORT CURRENT STATE\n\n**References Found in Codebase (17 files):**\n\n**Definition (src/shared/domain.rs):**\n- `FlowPreset::QuickDev` enum variant defined with string representation `\"quick_dev\"`\n- Description: \"Fast delivery flow for small code changes with lightweight review\"\n- Part of ALL_FLOWS constant with 4 presets: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n\n**Rejection Points (where quick_dev is blocked):**\n\n1. **src/cli/run.rs (lines 87-90, 169-172):**\n   ```rust\n   if matches!(project_record.flow, FlowPreset::QuickDev) {\n       return Err(AppError::UnsupportedFlow {\n           flow_id: project_record.flow.as_str().to_owned(),\n       });\n   }\n   ```\n   - Both `handle_start()` (line 87) and `handle_resume()` (line 169) reject quick_dev\n   - Happens AFTER config loading but BEFORE engine invocation\n   - Clean error message: \"flow 'quick_dev' is not yet supported for run execution\"\n\n2. **src/shared/error.rs (line 59):**\n   ```rust\n   UnsupportedFlow { flow_id: String },\n   ```\n   - Error message: \"flow '{flow_id}' is not yet supported for run execution; 'quick_dev' is deferred to a later loop\"\n\n**FlowSemantics Defined (src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs, lines 150-155):**\n```rust\nFlowPreset::QuickDev => FlowSemantics {\n    planning_stage: StageId::PlanAndImplement,\n    execution_stage: StageId::ApplyFixes,\n    remediation_trigger_stages: &QUICK_DEV_REMEDIATION_TRIGGER_STAGES,\n    late_stages: &QUICK_DEV_LATE_STAGES,\n    prompt_review_stage: None,\n}\n```\n\n**Stage Sequence Defined:**\n- 4 stages: PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview\n- Remediation triggers: [Review]\n- Late stages: [FinalReview]\n- No prompt_review_stage (unlike Standard flow)\n\n**Flow Definition (lines 91-100):**\n```rust\nFlowDefinition {\n    preset: FlowPreset::QuickDev,\n    description: \"Fast delivery flow for small code changes with lightweight review.\",\n    stages: &QUICK_DEV_STAGES,\n    validation_profile: ValidationProfile {\n        name: \"quick-dev-default\",\n        summary: \"Lightweight panel with final review enabled by default.\",\n        final_review_enabled: true,\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### 3. RUN.RS FILE - HOW RUN START AND RUN RESUME WORK\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` (389 lines)**\n\n**Structure:**\n- `RunCommand` subcommand router with 6 subcommands: Start, Resume, Status, History, Tail, Rollback\n- `handle()` dispatches to handlers (line 42)\n- Rollback not yet implemented\n\n**handle_start() Execution Flow (lines 73-157):**\n1. Get current directory (line 74)\n2. Load and validate workspace config (lines 77-78)\n3. Resolve active project (line 81)\n4. Load project record and **REJECT IF QUICK_DEV** (lines 85-91)\n5. Load run snapshot and validate status is \"not_started\" (lines 94-121)\n6. Load effective config (line 123)\n7. Build agent execution service (line 125)\n8. Call `engine::execute_run()` with:\n   - Agent service, snapshot read/write stores\n   - Journal store, artifact write store, log write store, amendment queue\n   - Project ID, flow preset, effective config\n9. Print final status\n\n**handle_resume() Execution Flow (lines 159-237):**\n- Same structure but:\n  - Validates status is \"failed\" or \"paused\" (not \"not_started\")\n  - Calls `engine::resume_run()` instead\n  - Uses FsArtifactStore in addition to write store\n\n**Key Rejection Logic:**\n- Quick_dev check at lines 87-91 and 169-172 uses simple pattern match\n- Happens immediately after project record load, before any mutations\n- Preconditions validation at lines 98-121 and 177-200\n  - Checks snapshot status matches expected state\n  - Checks no active run is already in progress\n\n**Engine Integration:**\n- Passes `project_record.flow` (FlowPreset) to engine\n- Engine calls: `execute_run()` or `resume_run()` in `contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs`\n- Both functions accept generic type parameters for adapter, output store, session store\n\n### 4. WORKFLOW ENGINE (engine.rs) - FLOW HANDLING\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` (2295 lines)**\n\n**Public Entrypoints:**\n- `execute_run()` (line 140) - top-level run start\n- `execute_run_with_retry()` (line 177) - with retry policy\n- `resume_run()` (line 377) - top-level run resume\n- `resume_run_with_retry()` (line 416) - with retry policy\n\n**Flow Support:**\n- Generic handling via `FlowPreset` parameter\n- `stage_plan_for_flow(preset, prompt_review_enabled)` resolves stage sequence (imported from mod.rs)\n- `flow_semantics(preset)` determines behavior traits (planning/execution/remediation stages)\n\n**Stage Plan Resolution (lines 224-231):**\n```rust\nlet stage_ids = stage_plan_for_flow(preset, effective_config.prompt_review_enabled());\nlet semantics = flow_semantics(preset);\nlet workspace_defaults = BackendSelectionConfig::from_effective_config(effective_config)?;\nlet stage_plan = resolve_stage_plan(\n    stage_ids.as_slice(),\n    agent_service.resolver(),\n    Some(&workspace_defaults),\n)?;\n```\n\n**Key Flow Elements:**\n- Stage plan derived from preset before any mutations\n- Preflight check validates all stages (line 232)\n- Journal event sequences track run progression\n- Amendment queue handles remediation between cycles\n- Cycle history and completion rounds tracked\n\n**No Special Quick_Dev Logic in Engine:**\n- Engine is preset-agnostic\n- All preset-specific logic is in stage plan and semantics definitions\n- Quick_dev is rejected at CLI level before reaching engine\n\n### 5. ERROR TYPES (src/shared/error.rs)\n\n**Key Error Variants:**\n\n```rust\n#[error(\n    \"unknown flow preset '{flow_id}'. supported presets: standard, quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement\"\n)]\nInvalidFlowPreset { flow_id: String },\n\n#[error(\"flow '{flow_id}' is not yet supported for run execution; 'quick_dev' is deferred to a later loop\")]\nUnsupportedFlow { flow_id: String },\n\n#[error(\"cannot start run: {reason}\")]\nRunStartFailed { reason: String },\n\n#[error(\"cannot resume run: {reason}\")]\nResumeFailed { reason: String },\n\n#[error(\"preflight check failed for stage '{stage_id}': {details}\")]\nPreflightFailed { stage_id: StageId, details: String },\n```\n\n**Flow-Related Errors:**\n- `InvalidFlowPreset` - for unknown flow IDs (config, parsing)\n- `UnsupportedFlow` - specific to quick_dev rejection at CLI run.rs level\n- No separate error variant for quick_dev (uses UnsupportedFlow)\n\n### 6. CONFORMANCE TEST FEATURES\n\n**Feature Files with Quick_Dev References:**\n\n**run_start_standard.feature (183 lines):**\n- Scenario SC-START-002 (line 19-24): \"Run start rejects quick_dev flow preset\"\n  ```gherkin\n  Given an initialized workspace with project \"beta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n  And project \"beta\" is selected as active\n  When the user runs \"run start\"\n  Then the command fails with error containing \"not yet supported\"\n  And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n  ```\n- Scenario SC-START-017 (line 140-144): Comprehensive multi-flow test\n  - Documents that standard, docs_change, ci_improvement succeed\n  - Explicitly states quick_dev fails with \"not yet supported\"\n\n**flow_discovery.feature (31 lines):**\n- Lists all 4 presets including quick_dev\n- Shows quick_dev stage sequence: plan_and_implement, review, apply_fixes, final_review\n- Confirms quick_dev can be discovered via `flow list` and `flow show`\n\n**daemon_routing.feature (62 lines):**\n- Tests routing to all flows including quick_dev\n- Scenario DAEMON-ROUTING-001: Command \"/rb flow quick_dev\" resolves correctly\n- Routing engine supports quick_dev as a valid flow resolution\n\n**workspace_config.feature:**\n- Tests setting `default_flow` to quick_dev via config command\n\n**run_resume_non_standard.feature:**\n- Tests resume behavior for non-standard flows (docs_change, ci_improvement)\n- Does NOT test quick_dev resume (because start is blocked)\n\n### 7. EXISTING UNIT TESTS\n\n**flow_semantics_test.rs (104 lines):**\n- `quick_dev_flow_semantics_are_defined()` (lines 26-34)\n- Validates semantics match spec for planning, execution, remediation, late stages\n- Tests that prompt_review_stage is None\n\n**flow_preset_test.rs (77 lines):**\n- `quick_dev_flow_stage_order_matches_spec()` (lines 40-49)\n- Validates stage sequence: [PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview]\n\n**config_test.rs (194 lines):**\n- `effective_config_merges_workspace_overrides()` (lines 36-76)\n- Tests setting default_flow to QuickDev (line 52)\n- Validates config persistence and loading\n\n**automation_runtime_test.rs (192 lines):**\n- `routing_resolution_prefers_command_over_label_and_default()` (lines 38-50)\n- Tests routing resolution with quick_dev command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n- Validates flow resolution works for daemon tasks\n\n**workflow_engine_test.rs (2932 lines):**\n- NO quick_dev specific tests\n- Tests standard flow comprehensively but not other flows\n\n### 8. CLI TEST FILE (tests/cli.rs)\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` (3609 lines)**\n\n**Quick_Dev References:**\n\n1. **Line 165, 725, 730:** Config commands support setting/reading quick_dev\n   ```rust\n   fn config_set_updates_valid_keys_and_rejects_invalid_values() {\n       let valid = Command::new(binary())\n           .args([\"config\", \"set\", \"default_flow\", \"quick_dev\"])\n       assert!(String::from_utf8_lossy(&valid.stdout).contains(\"Updated default_flow = quick_dev\"));\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Lines 940-944:** Project creation with quick_dev flow\n   ```rust\n   Command::new(binary())\n       .args([\n           \"project\", \"create\",\n           \"--name\", \"Beta\",\n           \"--prompt\", prompt.to_str().unwrap(),\n           \"--flow\", \"quick_dev\",\n       ])\n   ```\n\n3. **Lines 2888-2927:** Main quick_dev rejection test\n   ```rust\n   #[test]\n   fn run_start_rejects_quick_dev_flow() {\n       // Creates project with quick_dev flow\n       // Runs \"run start\"\n       // Asserts failure with error containing \"not yet supported\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Line 165, 1236:** Flow list includes quick_dev\n   ```rust\n   let stdout = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);\n   assert!(stdout.contains(\"quick_dev\"));\n   ```\n\n**Test Coverage Status:**\n- ✅ Flow discovery shows quick_dev\n- ✅ Config can set default_flow to quick_dev\n- ✅ Projects can be created with quick_dev flow\n- ✅ run start explicitly rejects quick_dev with appropriate error\n- ❌ run resume not tested (blocked by start rejection)\n- ❌ quick_dev execution tests (deferred to later loop)\n\n### 9. REQUIREMENTS DRAFTING CONTRACTS\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs` (238 lines)**\n\n**Quick_Dev Validation (lines 169-178):**\n```rust\n// Validate recommended_flow is a built-in preset\nlet valid_flows = [\n    FlowPreset::Standard,\n    FlowPreset::QuickDev,\n    FlowPreset::DocsChange,\n    FlowPreset::CiImprovement,\n];\nif !valid_flows.contains(&p.recommended_flow) {\n    errors.push(\"recommended_flow must be a built-in preset\".to_string());\n}\n```\n\n**Meaning:**\n- Requirements drafting stage can recommend quick_dev as output\n- But since run start blocks quick_dev, the recommendation cannot be acted upon\n- This is likely intentional - allow requirements to suggest it but block execution for now\n\n### 10. AUTOMATION RUNTIME & DAEMON SUPPORT\n\n**Current State:**\n- Daemon routing engine (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/routing.rs`) fully supports quick_dev\n- Tasks can be routed to quick_dev via command (\"/rb flow quick_dev\") or labels\n- Daemon task service accepts quick_dev as resolved flow\n- However, daemon dispatch still calls workflow engine which would hit run start rejection\n\n**Flow (in theory):**\n1. Daemon task created with quick_dev routing → succeeds\n2. Daemon claims task → succeeds\n3. Daemon dispatches task to engine → would fail at engine execution level\n\n**Testing:**\n- Unit tests verify routing works for quick_dev\n- Conformance tests verify daemon can route to quick_dev\n- CLI tests verify flow operations accept quick_dev\n\n### KEY INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Two-Layer Rejection:**\n   - CLI layer (run.rs) rejects quick_dev before engine execution\n   - Engine is ready and supports quick_dev semantics\n   - This is intentional - spec is for \"later loop\"\n\n2. **Complete Infrastructure:**\n   - Flow definition fully specified (stages, semantics, validation profile)\n   - Requirements can recommend quick_dev\n   - Daemon routing supports quick_dev\n   - Config can set quick_dev as default\n   - Tests document the rejection behavior\n\n3. **What's Missing for Full Quick_Dev Support:**\n   - Remove the UnsupportedFlow error check from run.rs (lines 87-91, 169-172)\n   - Likely no other changes needed - engine is preset-agnostic\n   - Conformance tests exist but are marked as testing rejection, not execution\n\n4. **Clean Separation:**\n   - Flow definitions in `workflow_composition/mod.rs`\n   - CLI rejection in `cli/run.rs`\n   - Engine logic in `engine.rs` (generic for all flows)\n   - This makes enable/disable toggle very clean\n\n### ABSOLUTE FILE PATHS\n\nKey files for the full picture:\n\n1. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - Quick_dev rejection logic\n2. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - Flow definitions and semantics\n3. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` - Workflow execution engine\n4. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - FlowPreset, StageId, stage semantics\n5. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - Error types\n6. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` - Configuration management\n7. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - CLI integration tests\n8. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature` - Conformance specs\n9. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_semantics_test.rs` - Flow semantics tests\n10. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_preset_test.rs` - Flow definition tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac51ef217f5c5066c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74396\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 95566</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"216e97eb-aa57-41df-a04f-9831b7c2815e","uuid":"72ebf983-5cc1-4983-84f8-8b214ecf9992","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (src/ layout, tests/ layout)\n2. The current state of quick_dev support - find all references to \"quick_dev\", \"UnsupportedFlow\", \"QuickDev\" in the codebase\n3. The CLI run.rs file - how run start and run resume work, especially where quick_dev is rejected\n4. The workflow engine (engine.rs) - how it handles different flow presets\n5. The error types in shared/error.rs\n6. Existing conformance test features related to quick_dev or run_start\n7. Existing unit tests for workflow engine and flow semantics\n8. The CLI test file tests/cli.rs\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files completely. I need the full picture of what exists and what needs to change.","agentId":"ac51ef217f5c5066c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document with all the findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: ralph-burning-rewrite Codebase\n\nI've thoroughly explored the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase and gathered complete information about the current state of the system. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Directory Layout:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/` - Main source code\n  - `cli/` - Command-line interface handlers (config, daemon, flow, init, project, requirements, run)\n  - `adapters/` - Filesystem, worktree, and stub backend adapters\n  - `contexts/` - Domain-specific contexts:\n    - `agent_execution/` - Backend invocation and session management\n    - `automation_runtime/` - Daemon task, lease, routing, and loop management\n    - `conformance_spec/` - Conformance feature specifications\n    - `project_run_record/` - Journal, snapshots, and run records\n    - `requirements_drafting/` - Requirements contracts and models\n    - `workflow_composition/` - Workflow engine, flow definitions, stage plans\n    - `workspace_governance/` - Workspace and project configuration\n  - `shared/` - Domain types (FlowPreset, StageId, error types)\n\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/` - Test suite\n  - `cli.rs` - Integration tests for CLI commands (3609 lines)\n  - `unit/` - Unit tests for core logic\n  - `conformance/features/` - Gherkin-based feature specifications (BDD tests)\n\n### 2. QUICK_DEV SUPPORT CURRENT STATE\n\n**References Found in Codebase (17 files):**\n\n**Definition (src/shared/domain.rs):**\n- `FlowPreset::QuickDev` enum variant defined with string representation `\"quick_dev\"`\n- Description: \"Fast delivery flow for small code changes with lightweight review\"\n- Part of ALL_FLOWS constant with 4 presets: Standard, QuickDev, DocsChange, CiImprovement\n\n**Rejection Points (where quick_dev is blocked):**\n\n1. **src/cli/run.rs (lines 87-90, 169-172):**\n   ```rust\n   if matches!(project_record.flow, FlowPreset::QuickDev) {\n       return Err(AppError::UnsupportedFlow {\n           flow_id: project_record.flow.as_str().to_owned(),\n       });\n   }\n   ```\n   - Both `handle_start()` (line 87) and `handle_resume()` (line 169) reject quick_dev\n   - Happens AFTER config loading but BEFORE engine invocation\n   - Clean error message: \"flow 'quick_dev' is not yet supported for run execution\"\n\n2. **src/shared/error.rs (line 59):**\n   ```rust\n   UnsupportedFlow { flow_id: String },\n   ```\n   - Error message: \"flow '{flow_id}' is not yet supported for run execution; 'quick_dev' is deferred to a later loop\"\n\n**FlowSemantics Defined (src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs, lines 150-155):**\n```rust\nFlowPreset::QuickDev => FlowSemantics {\n    planning_stage: StageId::PlanAndImplement,\n    execution_stage: StageId::ApplyFixes,\n    remediation_trigger_stages: &QUICK_DEV_REMEDIATION_TRIGGER_STAGES,\n    late_stages: &QUICK_DEV_LATE_STAGES,\n    prompt_review_stage: None,\n}\n```\n\n**Stage Sequence Defined:**\n- 4 stages: PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview\n- Remediation triggers: [Review]\n- Late stages: [FinalReview]\n- No prompt_review_stage (unlike Standard flow)\n\n**Flow Definition (lines 91-100):**\n```rust\nFlowDefinition {\n    preset: FlowPreset::QuickDev,\n    description: \"Fast delivery flow for small code changes with lightweight review.\",\n    stages: &QUICK_DEV_STAGES,\n    validation_profile: ValidationProfile {\n        name: \"quick-dev-default\",\n        summary: \"Lightweight panel with final review enabled by default.\",\n        final_review_enabled: true,\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### 3. RUN.RS FILE - HOW RUN START AND RUN RESUME WORK\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` (389 lines)**\n\n**Structure:**\n- `RunCommand` subcommand router with 6 subcommands: Start, Resume, Status, History, Tail, Rollback\n- `handle()` dispatches to handlers (line 42)\n- Rollback not yet implemented\n\n**handle_start() Execution Flow (lines 73-157):**\n1. Get current directory (line 74)\n2. Load and validate workspace config (lines 77-78)\n3. Resolve active project (line 81)\n4. Load project record and **REJECT IF QUICK_DEV** (lines 85-91)\n5. Load run snapshot and validate status is \"not_started\" (lines 94-121)\n6. Load effective config (line 123)\n7. Build agent execution service (line 125)\n8. Call `engine::execute_run()` with:\n   - Agent service, snapshot read/write stores\n   - Journal store, artifact write store, log write store, amendment queue\n   - Project ID, flow preset, effective config\n9. Print final status\n\n**handle_resume() Execution Flow (lines 159-237):**\n- Same structure but:\n  - Validates status is \"failed\" or \"paused\" (not \"not_started\")\n  - Calls `engine::resume_run()` instead\n  - Uses FsArtifactStore in addition to write store\n\n**Key Rejection Logic:**\n- Quick_dev check at lines 87-91 and 169-172 uses simple pattern match\n- Happens immediately after project record load, before any mutations\n- Preconditions validation at lines 98-121 and 177-200\n  - Checks snapshot status matches expected state\n  - Checks no active run is already in progress\n\n**Engine Integration:**\n- Passes `project_record.flow` (FlowPreset) to engine\n- Engine calls: `execute_run()` or `resume_run()` in `contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs`\n- Both functions accept generic type parameters for adapter, output store, session store\n\n### 4. WORKFLOW ENGINE (engine.rs) - FLOW HANDLING\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` (2295 lines)**\n\n**Public Entrypoints:**\n- `execute_run()` (line 140) - top-level run start\n- `execute_run_with_retry()` (line 177) - with retry policy\n- `resume_run()` (line 377) - top-level run resume\n- `resume_run_with_retry()` (line 416) - with retry policy\n\n**Flow Support:**\n- Generic handling via `FlowPreset` parameter\n- `stage_plan_for_flow(preset, prompt_review_enabled)` resolves stage sequence (imported from mod.rs)\n- `flow_semantics(preset)` determines behavior traits (planning/execution/remediation stages)\n\n**Stage Plan Resolution (lines 224-231):**\n```rust\nlet stage_ids = stage_plan_for_flow(preset, effective_config.prompt_review_enabled());\nlet semantics = flow_semantics(preset);\nlet workspace_defaults = BackendSelectionConfig::from_effective_config(effective_config)?;\nlet stage_plan = resolve_stage_plan(\n    stage_ids.as_slice(),\n    agent_service.resolver(),\n    Some(&workspace_defaults),\n)?;\n```\n\n**Key Flow Elements:**\n- Stage plan derived from preset before any mutations\n- Preflight check validates all stages (line 232)\n- Journal event sequences track run progression\n- Amendment queue handles remediation between cycles\n- Cycle history and completion rounds tracked\n\n**No Special Quick_Dev Logic in Engine:**\n- Engine is preset-agnostic\n- All preset-specific logic is in stage plan and semantics definitions\n- Quick_dev is rejected at CLI level before reaching engine\n\n### 5. ERROR TYPES (src/shared/error.rs)\n\n**Key Error Variants:**\n\n```rust\n#[error(\n    \"unknown flow preset '{flow_id}'. supported presets: standard, quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement\"\n)]\nInvalidFlowPreset { flow_id: String },\n\n#[error(\"flow '{flow_id}' is not yet supported for run execution; 'quick_dev' is deferred to a later loop\")]\nUnsupportedFlow { flow_id: String },\n\n#[error(\"cannot start run: {reason}\")]\nRunStartFailed { reason: String },\n\n#[error(\"cannot resume run: {reason}\")]\nResumeFailed { reason: String },\n\n#[error(\"preflight check failed for stage '{stage_id}': {details}\")]\nPreflightFailed { stage_id: StageId, details: String },\n```\n\n**Flow-Related Errors:**\n- `InvalidFlowPreset` - for unknown flow IDs (config, parsing)\n- `UnsupportedFlow` - specific to quick_dev rejection at CLI run.rs level\n- No separate error variant for quick_dev (uses UnsupportedFlow)\n\n### 6. CONFORMANCE TEST FEATURES\n\n**Feature Files with Quick_Dev References:**\n\n**run_start_standard.feature (183 lines):**\n- Scenario SC-START-002 (line 19-24): \"Run start rejects quick_dev flow preset\"\n  ```gherkin\n  Given an initialized workspace with project \"beta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n  And project \"beta\" is selected as active\n  When the user runs \"run start\"\n  Then the command fails with error containing \"not yet supported\"\n  And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n  ```\n- Scenario SC-START-017 (line 140-144): Comprehensive multi-flow test\n  - Documents that standard, docs_change, ci_improvement succeed\n  - Explicitly states quick_dev fails with \"not yet supported\"\n\n**flow_discovery.feature (31 lines):**\n- Lists all 4 presets including quick_dev\n- Shows quick_dev stage sequence: plan_and_implement, review, apply_fixes, final_review\n- Confirms quick_dev can be discovered via `flow list` and `flow show`\n\n**daemon_routing.feature (62 lines):**\n- Tests routing to all flows including quick_dev\n- Scenario DAEMON-ROUTING-001: Command \"/rb flow quick_dev\" resolves correctly\n- Routing engine supports quick_dev as a valid flow resolution\n\n**workspace_config.feature:**\n- Tests setting `default_flow` to quick_dev via config command\n\n**run_resume_non_standard.feature:**\n- Tests resume behavior for non-standard flows (docs_change, ci_improvement)\n- Does NOT test quick_dev resume (because start is blocked)\n\n### 7. EXISTING UNIT TESTS\n\n**flow_semantics_test.rs (104 lines):**\n- `quick_dev_flow_semantics_are_defined()` (lines 26-34)\n- Validates semantics match spec for planning, execution, remediation, late stages\n- Tests that prompt_review_stage is None\n\n**flow_preset_test.rs (77 lines):**\n- `quick_dev_flow_stage_order_matches_spec()` (lines 40-49)\n- Validates stage sequence: [PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview]\n\n**config_test.rs (194 lines):**\n- `effective_config_merges_workspace_overrides()` (lines 36-76)\n- Tests setting default_flow to QuickDev (line 52)\n- Validates config persistence and loading\n\n**automation_runtime_test.rs (192 lines):**\n- `routing_resolution_prefers_command_over_label_and_default()` (lines 38-50)\n- Tests routing resolution with quick_dev command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n- Validates flow resolution works for daemon tasks\n\n**workflow_engine_test.rs (2932 lines):**\n- NO quick_dev specific tests\n- Tests standard flow comprehensively but not other flows\n\n### 8. CLI TEST FILE (tests/cli.rs)\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` (3609 lines)**\n\n**Quick_Dev References:**\n\n1. **Line 165, 725, 730:** Config commands support setting/reading quick_dev\n   ```rust\n   fn config_set_updates_valid_keys_and_rejects_invalid_values() {\n       let valid = Command::new(binary())\n           .args([\"config\", \"set\", \"default_flow\", \"quick_dev\"])\n       assert!(String::from_utf8_lossy(&valid.stdout).contains(\"Updated default_flow = quick_dev\"));\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Lines 940-944:** Project creation with quick_dev flow\n   ```rust\n   Command::new(binary())\n       .args([\n           \"project\", \"create\",\n           \"--name\", \"Beta\",\n           \"--prompt\", prompt.to_str().unwrap(),\n           \"--flow\", \"quick_dev\",\n       ])\n   ```\n\n3. **Lines 2888-2927:** Main quick_dev rejection test\n   ```rust\n   #[test]\n   fn run_start_rejects_quick_dev_flow() {\n       // Creates project with quick_dev flow\n       // Runs \"run start\"\n       // Asserts failure with error containing \"not yet supported\"\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Line 165, 1236:** Flow list includes quick_dev\n   ```rust\n   let stdout = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);\n   assert!(stdout.contains(\"quick_dev\"));\n   ```\n\n**Test Coverage Status:**\n- ✅ Flow discovery shows quick_dev\n- ✅ Config can set default_flow to quick_dev\n- ✅ Projects can be created with quick_dev flow\n- ✅ run start explicitly rejects quick_dev with appropriate error\n- ❌ run resume not tested (blocked by start rejection)\n- ❌ quick_dev execution tests (deferred to later loop)\n\n### 9. REQUIREMENTS DRAFTING CONTRACTS\n\n**File: `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs` (238 lines)**\n\n**Quick_Dev Validation (lines 169-178):**\n```rust\n// Validate recommended_flow is a built-in preset\nlet valid_flows = [\n    FlowPreset::Standard,\n    FlowPreset::QuickDev,\n    FlowPreset::DocsChange,\n    FlowPreset::CiImprovement,\n];\nif !valid_flows.contains(&p.recommended_flow) {\n    errors.push(\"recommended_flow must be a built-in preset\".to_string());\n}\n```\n\n**Meaning:**\n- Requirements drafting stage can recommend quick_dev as output\n- But since run start blocks quick_dev, the recommendation cannot be acted upon\n- This is likely intentional - allow requirements to suggest it but block execution for now\n\n### 10. AUTOMATION RUNTIME & DAEMON SUPPORT\n\n**Current State:**\n- Daemon routing engine (`src/contexts/automation_runtime/routing.rs`) fully supports quick_dev\n- Tasks can be routed to quick_dev via command (\"/rb flow quick_dev\") or labels\n- Daemon task service accepts quick_dev as resolved flow\n- However, daemon dispatch still calls workflow engine which would hit run start rejection\n\n**Flow (in theory):**\n1. Daemon task created with quick_dev routing → succeeds\n2. Daemon claims task → succeeds\n3. Daemon dispatches task to engine → would fail at engine execution level\n\n**Testing:**\n- Unit tests verify routing works for quick_dev\n- Conformance tests verify daemon can route to quick_dev\n- CLI tests verify flow operations accept quick_dev\n\n### KEY INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Two-Layer Rejection:**\n   - CLI layer (run.rs) rejects quick_dev before engine execution\n   - Engine is ready and supports quick_dev semantics\n   - This is intentional - spec is for \"later loop\"\n\n2. **Complete Infrastructure:**\n   - Flow definition fully specified (stages, semantics, validation profile)\n   - Requirements can recommend quick_dev\n   - Daemon routing supports quick_dev\n   - Config can set quick_dev as default\n   - Tests document the rejection behavior\n\n3. **What's Missing for Full Quick_Dev Support:**\n   - Remove the UnsupportedFlow error check from run.rs (lines 87-91, 169-172)\n   - Likely no other changes needed - engine is preset-agnostic\n   - Conformance tests exist but are marked as testing rejection, not execution\n\n4. **Clean Separation:**\n   - Flow definitions in `workflow_composition/mod.rs`\n   - CLI rejection in `cli/run.rs`\n   - Engine logic in `engine.rs` (generic for all flows)\n   - This makes enable/disable toggle very clean\n\n### ABSOLUTE FILE PATHS\n\nKey files for the full picture:\n\n1. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - Quick_dev rejection logic\n2. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - Flow definitions and semantics\n3. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` - Workflow execution engine\n4. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - FlowPreset, StageId, stage semantics\n5. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - Error types\n6. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` - Configuration management\n7. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - CLI integration tests\n8. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature` - Conformance specs\n9. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_semantics_test.rs` - Flow semantics tests\n10. `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_preset_test.rs` - Flow definition tests"}],"totalDurationMs":95566,"totalTokens":74396,"totalToolUseCount":38,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1058,"cache_read_input_tokens":68760,"output_tokens":4577,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1058},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
